	     Cairo - An Egyptian security official says 14 policemen have been killed in a shootout with militants southwest Cairo. The official says the exchange of gunfire took place on Friday in the al-Wahat al-Bahriya district in the Giza governorate, about 135km from the Egyptian capital. He says eight other security personnel were wounded in the attack. Several Egyptian media outlets also reported the shootout. The official spoke on condition of anonymity because he was not authorised to talk to reporters. Several Egyptian media outlets reported the deadly shootout. No militant group immediately claimed involvement in Friday's shootout. Egypt has been under a state of emergency since bombings and suicide attacks targeting minority Coptic Christians killed scores earlier this year. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  